7) Replication types in PostgreSQL?
- Physical Replication → WAL-level, full cluster copy (streaming, synchronous, asynchronous).
- Logical Replication → Table-level, selective, flexible (publish/subscribe).
- Snapshot Replication → Initial data copy.
- Cascading Replication → Standby-to-standby replication.

8) Replication data types in PostgreSQL
- Physical replication → WAL-level, binary data blocks.
- Logical replication → Row-level, SQL operations.
- Snapshot replication → Initial bulk data copy.
- Cascading replication → Standby-to-standby WAL forwarding.

