37) why vacuum full not performed in production?
ACUUM FULL is not typically performed in production because it requires an exclusive lock on the table and rewrites the entire file, which can cause downtime 
and heavy I/O load. Instead, we rely on autovacuum for routine cleanup, and if we need to reclaim disk space, 
we use tools like pg_repack that achieve similar results without blocking queries.

