42) Authentication types?
PostgreSQL supports multiple authentication methods, ranging from simple trust-based access to advanced Kerberos/GSSAPI integration. 
The choice depends on your environment (development, production, cloud, enterprise security). 
The most common are password-based (md5, scram-sha-256), trust, and host-based authentication via pg_hba.conf.

